second_review_general_comments: This is the third year in a row (ie 2011, 2012, and now 2013) that applicant has applied to our school.  I have reviewed all three applications, looked at all three resumes, and read all three SOPs.  She has done two things differently since 2011: she has been volunteering at two SW-related agencies; and she took three post-grad courses at CSULA, for which she earned good grades.  The SOP for each of the three applications is very similar: each time, she writes that her very poor undergrad grades are due to her "passionately fighting social injustice." Each of the three SOPs also notes that her focus is now on academics, and that we should just believe her on THAT.  Given her sheer persistence, and that she has indeed done some things to try to advance her knowledge and experience, I recommend our Admissions staff call her in for an interview. It is somewhat possible the applicant is "better" than her application would indicate...
